<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idf67a605b-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s7309"><num value="7309">§ 7309.</num><heading> Able seamen—special</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The required service for the endorsement of able seaman—special, qualified for special service on a vessel on any waters, is at least 6 months <ref class="footnoteRef" idref="fn002010">1</ref><note type="footnote" id="fn002010"><num>1</num> So in original. Probably should be “6 months’ ”.</note> service on deck on board vessels operating on the oceans or the navigable waters of the United States (including the Great Lakes).</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idf67a605c-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5">(<ref href="/us/pl/98/89">Pub. L. 98–89</ref>, <date date="1983-08-26">Aug. 26, 1983</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/97/543">97 Stat. 543</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/119/60/dG/tLXXIII/s7301/d/4">Pub. L. 119–60, div. G, title LXXIII, § 7301(d)(4)</ref>, <date date="2025-12-18">Dec. 18, 2025</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/139/1754">139 Stat. 1754</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idf67a605d-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5">
<note topic="historicalAndRevision" id="idf67a605e-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5">
